---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { url } from '../../lib/paths';
---

<PageLayout
  title="For trainers"
  description="How to use Free Ham Radio Curriculum materials to lead workshops in your club or community."
  current="start"
>
  <Breadcrumbs
    items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'For trainers' },
    ]}
  />
  <h1>For trainers</h1>
  <p>
    Free Ham Radio Curriculum is a set of ready-to-lead workshops and activities — not an online course. You
    download materials, gather a group, and teach in person.
  </p>

  <h2>How this site is organized</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/')}>Curriculum</a>: All workshops and activities</li>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/phone/')}>Phone track</a> and <a href={url('/curriculum/digital/')}>Digital track</a>: Courses to bring learners to HF</li>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/activities/')}>Activities</a>: Standalone events that can be done in any order</li>
    <li><a href={url('/reference/cheat-sheets/')}>Cheat sheets</a>: Laminate-friendly references</li>
    <li><a href={url('/downloads/')}>Downloads</a>: Every document in one place</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>It's this easy to use this curriculum</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Every unit has a one-page overview; skim that and the slides (5–15 minutes)</li>
    <li>Print handouts for learners and any required cheat sheets</li>
    <li>Workshops require a projector, some activities need an outdoor space</li>
    <li>Good for groups of 5–95; sessions run from one to two hours</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="suggested-sequences">Suggested sequences</h2>
  <p>
    You do not have to commit to a complete phone or digital course, beginning to end! Below are some bite-sized chunks you can start from.
  </p>

  <div class="card-grid card-grid-2" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <div class="card card-static">
      <h3>Community intro</h3>
      <p>Emergency Radio 101 + Fox Hunt</p>
      <p>2–3 hours · No license</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-static">
      <h3>Get on the air! (phone)</h3>
      <p>GMRS 101 + Practical Radio Skills</p>
      <p>2–3 hours · No license</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-static">
      <h3>Intro to Ham</h3>
      <p>Ham 101 + Ham HT Practical Skills</p>
      <p>2–3 hours · No license (Technician ok)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-static">
      <h3>Intro to digital radio</h3>
      <p>Mesh Networks 101 + Digital Radio 101 + Mesh Network Practical Skills</p>
      <p>4.5 hours · No license</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-static">
      <h3>Ham radio deep dive</h3>
      <p>Ham 201 + Ham HF Practical Skills</p>
      <p>2–3 hours · General</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-static">
      <h3>Emcomm afternoon</h3>
      <p>Emergency Radio 101 + PACE Planning + How to Host a Neighborhood Net</p>
      <p>4-5 hours · No license</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <h3>Do I need to be an ARRL instructor?</h3>
  <p>No. Any experienced Ham who can follow the trainer guide can lead these sessions.</p>
  <h3>Can I run just one workshop?</h3>
  <p>Yes. Especially the first three phone workshops and first two digital workshops — no license required.</p>
  <h3>Can I change the slides?</h3>
  <p>Materials are CC BY-SA. Adapt for your community; credit the source.</p>

  <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href={url('/curriculum/')}>Browse curriculum</a>
    {' '}
    <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={url('/downloads/')}>Downloads</a>
  </p>
</PageLayout>
